# Article Structure Guide

Articles in this project follow a specific structure to ensure consistency and quality.

## Directory Structure

Each article has its own directory in [content/](mdc:content/) with the following structure:
- `index.md` - The main article content with frontmatter
- `perplexity-data.json` - Research data from Perplexity
- `paa-data.json` - People Also Ask data
- `serper-data.json` - Search result data
- `images-data.json` - Image ideas and URLs

Example: [content/value-of-art/](mdc:content/value-of-art/)

## Article Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Article Title"
description: "Brief description for SEO"
date: 2025-01-01T10:00:00-04:00
lastmod: 2025-01-01T10:00:00-04:00
draft: false
slug: "article-slug"
categories: ["Category"]
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
keywords: ["keyword1", "keyword2"]
---
```

## Common Article Sections

1. Introduction
2. Main content sections with appropriate headings
3. FAQ section
4. Image gallery
5. Resource links

## Content Creation Workflow

1. Research data is collected in JSON files
2. Article structure is planned based on research
3. Content is written using appropriate shortcodes
4. Images are added using the image gallery shortcode
5. SEO metadata is optimized
